00:20:18,429 --> 00:20:19,763
My dowry is secured.

272
00:20:27,054 --> 00:20:28,971
You'll help find Minnie for me, won't you?

273
00:20:29,429 --> 00:20:30,512
Yes.

274
00:20:34,304 --> 00:20:35,179
But it will be expensive.

275
00:20:36,804 --> 00:20:37,637
One million dollars.

276
00:20:39,096 --> 00:20:41,762
- I thought you said 500,000 dollars.
- Are you kidding? No way!

277
00:20:42,929 --> 00:20:46,845
I'm the God of Cracking Cases.

278
00:20:47,762 --> 00:20:49,137
- Do you have any problem?
- No.

279
00:20:50,595 --> 00:20:51,512
Apply for your leave.

280
00:20:53,054 --> 00:20:53,970
Why would I do that?

281
00:20:54,137 --> 00:20:55,679
You can learn from me.

282
00:20:55,887 --> 00:20:57,178
I'll teach you a few clever tricks.

283
00:20:57,262 --> 00:20:58,512
Free of charge.

284
00:20:59,553 --> 00:21:01,678
- Thank you, thank you.
- My pleasure.

285
00:21:02,512 --> 00:21:04,220
Listen to this case.

286
00:21:04,887 --> 00:21:05,803
<i>Homicide case.</i>

287
00:21:05,887 --> 00:21:07,887
<i>April 17, 1992.</i>

288
00:21:07,970 --> 00:21:09,053
<i>Wednesday night.</i>

289
00:21:09,137 --> 00:21:10,262
<i>Kowloon public morgue.</i>

290
00:21:28,178 --> 00:21:29,011
Police!

291
00:21:39,261 --> 00:21:40,886
You'll be Kau. I'll be Tak.

292
00:21:41,011 --> 00:21:42,552
- Tell me I'm stupid.
- How?

293
00:21:42,636 --> 00:21:43,927
Brainless! Moron!

294
00:21:45,719 --> 00:21:47,469
Use your imagination.

295
00:21:49,802 --> 00:21:52,719
Brainless! Moron!

296
00:21:53,552 --> 00:21:56,469
Brainless! Moron!

297
00:21:56,844 --> 00:21:58,719
- Brainless!
- Do you think with your ass?

298
00:21:58,927 --> 00:22:00,177
Pig!

299
00:22:02,760 --> 00:22:04,969
Do you think with your ass? Pig!

300
00:22:05,052 --> 00:22:06,844
Again, fiercer.

301
00:22:08,677 --> 00:22:10,260
Dickhead!

302
00:22:10,343 --> 00:22:11,260
Pig!

303
00:22:11,343 --> 00:22:13,343
Kau is from Chiuchow. Use the dialect.

304
00:22:16,635 --> 00:22:18,802
Dickhead!

305
00:22:18,885 --> 00:22:20,010
Pig!

306
00:22:20,093 --> 00:22:21,718
You know nothing!

307
00:22:21,885 --> 00:22:23,427
You aren't human!

308
00:22:23,510 --> 00:22:25,551
You're as stupid as a pig!

309
00:22:25,676 --> 00:22:27,010
You know nothing!

310
00:22:27,176 --> 00:22:28,468
Dickhead!

311
00:22:28,551 --> 00:22:30,635
Moron! Have you left your brain at home?

312
00:22:30,801 --> 00:22:33,051
I've told you. You imbecile!

313
00:22:33,135 --> 00:22:35,385
Let me tell you, you're worse than a pig!

314
00:22:35,468 --> 00:22:36,926
As stupid as a pig!

315
00:22:37,010 --> 00:22:38,510
Your brain is full of shit!

316
00:22:38,593 --> 00:22:40,259
Asshole, have you finished?

317
00:22:42,343 --> 00:22:43,176
What?

318
00:22:47,468 --> 00:22:48,634
It doesn't break.

319
00:22:50,509 --> 00:22:51,884
I'll throw it harder.

320
00:22:52,134 --> 00:22:52,968
Let's swap roles.

321
00:22:53,051 --> 00:22:54,801
I'll play Tak, and you'll play Kau.

322
00:22:58,551 --> 00:23:00,634
Asshole, have you finished?

323
00:23:01,717 --> 00:23:02,551
What happened?

324
00:23:02,634 --> 00:23:03,717
It didn't break.

325
00:23:03,801 --> 00:23:04,676
Forget it.

326
00:23:04,759 --> 00:23:05,842
Let's start again.

327
00:23:11,217 --> 00:23:12,842
Asshole, have you finished?

328
00:23:14,050 --> 00:23:17,717
Did you bring your brain to work?

329
00:23:28,883 --> 00:23:29,967
Wait!

330
00:23:31,425 --> 00:23:32,258
Wait a second.

331
00:23:32,717 --> 00:23:35,633
A person like you who has learned
martial arts won't be able to do it.

332
00:23:37,758 --> 00:23:38,675
Let's swap.

333
00:23:39,466 --> 00:23:40,550
But you can't see.

334
00:23:40,633 --> 00:23:42,383
It's okay. I'll manage.

335
00:23:56,341 --> 00:23:59,466
Crawl! Hurry!

336
00:24:02,174 --> 00:24:05,258
Faster!

337
00:24:09,466 --> 00:24:12,049
Tak is coming from behind,
like someone insane.

338
00:24:12,132 --> 00:24:13,174
He hit him nine times.

339
00:24:13,257 --> 00:24:14,341
One, two...

340
00:24:17,132 --> 00:24:18,424
Stop!

341
00:24:21,132 --> 00:24:23,091
Kau was seriously injured.

342
00:24:23,216 --> 00:24:24,924
He couldn't have crawled so fast.

343
00:24:25,424 --> 00:24:28,799
Back to the original position.
Act slowly this time.

344
00:24:29,049 --> 00:24:30,132
You're badly injured.

345
00:24:32,632 --> 00:24:33,715
You're doomed.

346
00:24:39,173 --> 00:24:43,090
Keep crawling.

347
00:24:43,590 --> 00:24:45,507
You're a piece of dead meat now.

348
00:24:50,298 --> 00:24:52,215
Stop!

349
00:24:52,298 --> 00:24:53,173
What?

350
00:24:53,382 --> 00:24:56,131
You're inconsistent.
You were mad just a while ago.

351
00:24:56,215 --> 00:24:59,048
Why are you acting like that now?

352
00:24:59,131 --> 00:25:01,131
It's not right for you to strike him,

353
00:25:01,465 --> 00:25:02,381
and then waited

354
00:25:02,756 --> 00:25:04,381
before you hit him
nine more times outside.

355
00:25:04,756 --> 00:25:06,006
What happened in between?

356
00:25:08,423 --> 00:25:09,256
The delivery man came?

357
00:25:10,839 --> 00:25:12,048
Who ordered from us?

358
00:25:15,673 --> 00:25:16,589
Diarrhea?

359
00:25:23,464 --> 00:25:25,547
What's more urgent than killing a person?

360
00:25:31,131 --> 00:25:32,256
To kill another person.

361
00:25:33,214 --> 00:25:34,297
There's a third person.

362
00:25:35,256 --> 00:25:37,131
A third person entered the scene

363
00:25:37,214 --> 00:25:38,255
after Tak had hit Kau once.

364
00:25:38,589 --> 00:25:39,964
Tak had to leave Kau behind

365
00:25:40,047 --> 00:25:41,339
and chase after that third person.

366
00:25:43,339 --> 00:25:44,255
I need a third person.

367
00:25:44,339 --> 00:25:45,214
Here!

368
00:25:46,089 --> 00:25:46,922
Let me play him.

369
00:25:47,755 --> 00:25:49,047
Wait, no!

370
00:25:49,297 --> 00:25:51,589
The police didn't find
any other bloodstain at the crime scene.

371
00:25:52,047 --> 00:25:54,963
Tak didn't kill with a hammer.

372
00:26:00,213 --> 00:26:01,422
The victim was strangled to death.

373
00:26:01,588 --> 00:26:02,797
The timing fits.

374
00:26:03,255 --> 00:26:04,338
Get one of them to play Kau.

375
00:26:04,422 --> 00:26:05,255
- Me.
- Me.

376
00:26:05,338 --> 00:26:06,797
- You! You raised your hand first.
- Yes.

377
00:26:10,463 --> 00:26:13,463
When I start strangling, start crawling.

378
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:19,713
Can I struggle?

379
00:26:19,796 --> 00:26:21,463
Of course. That's normal.

380
00:26:22,213 --> 00:26:23,088
It hurts!

381
00:26:23,463 --> 00:26:24,754
Ouch!

382
00:26:26,171 --> 00:26:27,379
You can't strangle me like this.

383
00:26:27,463 --> 00:26:28,463
Let's swap.

384
00:26:28,588 --> 00:26:29,463
I'm blind!

385
00:26:29,546 --> 00:26:30,421
All right!

386
00:26:30,504 --> 00:26:31,629
Again?

387
00:26:31,796 --> 00:26:32,838
Yes.

388
00:26:33,171 --> 00:26:34,296
I'm blind!

389
00:26:34,421 --> 00:26:35,963
I know. One, two, three.

390
00:26:48,421 --> 00:26:50,004
Sorry. I played it for real.

391
00:26:51,837 --> 00:26:54,462
After him!

392
00:27:02,045 --> 00:27:06,420
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine!

393
00:27:06,504 --> 00:27:07,337
Dead!

394
00:27:07,420 --> 00:27:09,212
The time matches!

395
00:27:11,045 --> 00:27:12,087
Johnston?

396
00:27:22,295 --> 00:27:23,920
Who's the one being strangled?

397
00:27:26,503 --> 00:27:27,836
The police didn't find his body.

398
00:27:28,711 --> 00:27:29,920
That means you've disposed of it.

399
00:27:30,753 --> 00:27:31,920
Why did you dispose of this guy

400
00:27:32,045 --> 00:27:33,128
but not him?

401
00:27:37,336 --> 00:27:39,586
Where have you been
in the last two decades?

402
00:27:56,252 --> 00:27:58,419
Higher. Ready? Drop it.

403
00:28:05,877 --> 00:28:07,669
Right. That's the way it was smashed.

404
00:28:08,044 --> 00:28:10,169
But why smash the TV?

405
00:28:10,294 --> 00:28:11,627
What triggered such behavior?

406
00:28:19,835 --> 00:28:25,210
What program was aired on
Wednesday nights 20 years ago?

407
00:28:26,002 --> 00:28:27,043
<i>Enjoy Yourself Tonight.</i>

408
00:28:27,793 --> 00:28:28,877
What about in other channels?

409
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:30,752
Live broadcast of horse-racing.

410
00:28:30,835 --> 00:28:31,752
I understand now!

411
00:28:33,127 --> 00:28:34,252
I completely understand.

412
00:28:36,876 --> 00:28:38,793
Let's go and eat.

413
00:28:40,376 --> 00:28:41,751
We won't need these. Thank you.

414
00:28:51,459 --> 00:28:53,126
- Here's the change, two dollars.
- Thanks.

415
00:28:59,084 --> 00:29:00,334
Two bowls of noodles.

416
00:29:00,751 --> 00:29:04,293
Long time no see. I thought you were dead.

417
00:29:04,501 --> 00:29:05,834
{\an8}KEI KEE

418
00:29:06,959 --> 00:29:09,084
This is super delicious.

419
00:29:09,334 --> 00:29:11,751
I used to come here with Szeto.

420
00:29:16,251 --> 00:29:17,459
Do you see

421
00:29:17,667 --> 00:29:19,751
that there is a dance studio
on the second floor behind you?

422
00:29:21,500 --> 00:29:22,417
Do you see it?

423
00:29:22,500 --> 00:29:25,084
Yes. Tango Blue, right?

424
00:29:29,667 --> 00:29:31,250
Go check if she's there.

425
00:29:31,500 --> 00:29:32,917
- Go.
- What's the case about?

426
00:29:33,125 --> 00:29:34,625
A big case. Go.

427
00:29:34,709 --> 00:29:35,583
Okay.

428
00:29:35,708 --> 00:29:37,417
- Don't fuck it up.
- Yes.

429
00:29:45,917 --> 00:29:46,875
She's coming down.

430
00:29:47,500 --> 00:29:48,500
Who?

431
00:29:48,792 --> 00:29:50,875
The lady, what shall we do?

432
00:29:54,166 --> 00:29:55,875
Don't look. Pretend to eat.

433
00:30:01,125 --> 00:30:02,166
Calm down.

434
00:30:06,291 --> 00:30:10,124
Seems like you're the nervous one.
Who's she?

435
00:30:10,249 --> 00:30:11,416
A wanted criminal?

436
00:30:52,123 --> 00:30:55,248
She's getting in a cab.
Shall we follow her?

437
00:30:56,623 --> 00:30:57,623
Johnston?

438
00:30:58,665 --> 00:31:01,290
No need. Mission accomplished.

439
00:31:02,540 --> 00:31:05,165
Two more bowls for takeaway, please.

440
00:31:05,248 --> 00:31:06,081
Okay.

441
00:31:14,123 --> 00:31:17,123
Hey, take off your shoes.

442
00:31:17,206 --> 00:31:18,581
I just washed the floor.

443
00:31:24,623 --> 00:31:25,498
What's up?

444
00:31:25,581 --> 00:31:26,831
Why are you so excited?

445
00:31:27,456 --> 00:31:29,039
She's back.

446
00:31:30,831 --> 00:31:32,123
Who?

447
00:31:43,122 --> 00:31:46,581
This is nice, who are you talking about?

448
00:31:47,539 --> 00:31:48,414
What are you eating?

449
00:31:50,080 --> 00:31:51,247
Gizzard.

450
00:31:51,330 --> 00:31:52,664
What dance am I dancing?

451
00:31:53,747 --> 00:31:54,705
Tango.

452
00:32:01,622 --> 00:32:02,580
Your future wife?

453
00:32:02,789 --> 00:32:05,080
Right. My future wife.

454
00:32:05,163 --> 00:32:06,163
Don't you remember?

455
00:32:06,663 --> 00:32:08,163
You helped me find her back then.

456
00:32:08,247 --> 00:32:09,288
But she went away.

457
00:32:09,955 --> 00:32:12,497
I've never thought
I'd run into her four years later.

458
00:32:12,622 --> 00:32:15,372
I'm destined to marry her.

459
00:32:18,122 --> 00:32:19,288
Have you ever thought

460
00:32:19,663 --> 00:32:21,538
your future wife might have married?

461
00:32:21,830 --> 00:32:23,746
You have a foul mouth.

462
00:32:23,830 --> 00:32:25,163
She's probably someone else's wife.

463
00:32:26,413 --> 00:32:27,955
It's been a long time,
and she's 30 already.

464
00:32:28,955 --> 00:32:30,705
It's perfectly normal to get married.

465
00:32:30,788 --> 00:32:32,163
A beautiful woman like her

466
00:32:32,246 --> 00:32:34,829
must have a lot of suitors.

467
00:32:36,829 --> 00:32:38,871
Right.

468
00:32:38,954 --> 00:32:41,204
Harder!

469
00:32:41,288 --> 00:32:42,996
Okay!

470
00:32:52,537 --> 00:32:55,662
It's all mold and rot.

471
00:32:56,162 --> 00:32:58,912
One can't live here anymore.

472
00:33:00,079 --> 00:33:01,537
I'm not used to work outside of my house.

473
00:33:01,621 --> 00:33:04,412
But this is a complicated case.

474
00:33:04,662 --> 00:33:06,120
I need to move out and feel things.

475
00:33:06,704 --> 00:33:07,787
No additional charge.

476
00:33:08,120 --> 00:33:09,662
Sure. Thanks a lot.

477
00:33:10,079 --> 00:33:11,037
My pleasure.

478
00:33:13,245 --> 00:33:14,329
Where's my room?

479
00:33:20,078 --> 00:33:21,828
What do you think, Johnston?
Is everything okay?

480
00:33:22,287 --> 00:33:24,370
It will do.

481
00:33:24,620 --> 00:33:26,995
I'd like my wardrobe
to be set up just like the way at home.

482
00:33:27,578 --> 00:33:30,412
Suits on the left and shirts on the right.

483
00:33:30,703 --> 00:33:32,953
Casual wear and pajamas in the bottom.

484
00:33:52,328 --> 00:33:56,369
Let's watch TV together, Goldie.

485
00:34:22,285 --> 00:34:23,202
Johnston?

486
00:34:24,202 --> 00:34:26,077
- Johnston.
- I'm thinking about something.

487
00:34:32,993 --> 00:34:34,410
You were looking at Minnie from here?

488
00:34:38,035 --> 00:34:39,285
She was standing across the street.

489
00:34:39,577 --> 00:34:41,410
Go down and shout to me.
I'd like to experience it.

490
00:34:42,202 --> 00:34:43,160
Okay.

491
00:34:53,368 --> 00:34:56,160
Johnston! I'm here!

492
00:34:56,785 --> 00:34:57,701
Good.

493
00:35:05,118 --> 00:35:05,993
Hello?

494
00:35:06,576 --> 00:35:07,826
Did Minnie behave strangely

495
00:35:08,159 --> 00:35:09,451
while she was waiting for you?

496
00:35:10,034 --> 00:35:12,243
She came here right after school.

497
00:35:12,451 --> 00:35:14,076
She did that for several nights.

498
00:35:14,743 --> 00:35:16,326
But I remember that on the last night,

499
00:35:16,409 --> 00:35:19,909
she was raising her hand at me.

500
00:35:20,117 --> 00:35:21,576
I didn't know what that meant.

501
00:35:21,826 --> 00:35:22,742
She slit her wrist.

502
00:35:25,367 --> 00:35:27,659
She wanted me
to know she was very unhappy.

503
00:35:28,784 --> 00:35:30,367
Why didn't I realize that?

504
00:35:30,742 --> 00:35:32,575
And yet you knew right away.

505
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:34,992
I'm blind, but I can read people's mind.

506
00:35:36,867 --> 00:35:38,075
Why are you blind?

507
00:35:40,159 --> 00:35:41,367
I was on a case

508
00:35:41,617 --> 00:35:42,659
four years ago,

509
00:35:43,742 --> 00:35:45,409
I was waiting for the suspect
to show his face.

510
00:35:45,950 --> 00:35:47,533
I started to see dark patches

511
00:35:47,825 --> 00:35:48,908
on the seventh day.

512
00:35:49,492 --> 00:35:53,075
But I didn't pay any attention to that
since I wanted to solve the case.

513
00:35:53,700 --> 00:35:55,617
The next day, the suspect showed up

514
00:35:55,992 --> 00:35:58,575
I chased frantically after him
until I caught him.

515
00:35:59,867 --> 00:36:03,741
But I became blind after that.

516
00:36:04,700 --> 00:36:06,616
The doctor said it's retinal detachment,

517
00:36:07,408 --> 00:36:09,741
and it's too late.

518
00:36:24,116 --> 00:36:25,449
Which one is Minnie?

519
00:36:29,658 --> 00:36:33,741
Check whose feet will fit the sneaker.

520
00:36:35,532 --> 00:36:37,491
Minnie's feet have grown so much?

521
00:36:37,657 --> 00:36:39,157
I gave her a pair of red shoes.

522
00:36:44,532 --> 00:36:46,699
This is the police. Line up.

523
00:36:46,990 --> 00:36:49,324
Take off your shoes, one by one.

524
00:36:50,532 --> 00:36:51,574
Left foot, please.

525
00:37:02,865 --> 00:37:03,782
What's up?

526
00:37:04,240 --> 00:37:05,198
Coach, it's the police.

527
00:37:05,657 --> 00:37:07,157
We're on a case. Step aside.

528
00:37:21,281 --> 00:37:23,490
What's wrong? What happened?

529
00:37:23,573 --> 00:37:24,781
The coach ran away.

530
00:37:25,156 --> 00:37:27,281
Chase after her.

531
00:37:27,365 --> 00:37:28,448
- Okay!
- After her.

532
00:37:32,114 --> 00:37:34,156
Bingo. I can't believe it.

533
00:37:35,614 --> 00:37:38,364
Take a break. More policemen are coming.

534
00:37:42,614 --> 00:37:43,448
<i>Hello?</i>

535
00:37:43,573 --> 00:37:45,906
I told you, Szeto.

536
00:37:46,156 --> 00:37:48,822
That big-foot who robbed
five jewelry shops in a row

537
00:37:51,156 --> 00:37:54,364
three years ago is a woman.

538
00:37:54,447 --> 00:37:55,614
Come quickly.

539
00:37:55,697 --> 00:37:58,239
Minnie!

540
00:38:12,655 --> 00:38:14,405
Are you okay, miss?

541
00:38:20,780 --> 00:38:22,072
Minnie!

542
00:38:25,322 --> 00:38:26,988
Minnie!

543
00:38:36,571 --> 00:38:38,946
I lost her. I only picked up a shoe.

544
00:38:41,488 --> 00:38:42,821
Why do you give it to me?

545
00:38:43,071 --> 00:38:46,154
I thought you're a sprinter?

546
00:38:46,321 --> 00:38:47,863
She was much taller than me.

547
00:38:47,946 --> 00:38:51,071
She doubled my strides.
I even broke my heels.

548
00:38:51,154 --> 00:38:53,154
Why didn't you shoot her?

549
00:38:53,363 --> 00:38:54,696
You also mentioned your marksmanship.

