01:14:16,232 --> 01:14:18,190
Can you get into the character?
You can do it, right?

1091
01:14:42,814 --> 01:14:43,648
What's wrong?

1092
01:14:43,731 --> 01:14:46,523
I can't get into character
if I restrain myself.

1093
01:14:47,106 --> 01:14:48,773
Let's play it for real. Just once.

1094
01:14:49,856 --> 01:14:50,856
All right.

1095
01:14:58,481 --> 01:14:59,397
Why?

1096
01:14:59,772 --> 01:15:01,772
Why did two people so much in love

1097
01:15:04,147 --> 01:15:05,939
would end up like this?

1098
01:15:06,855 --> 01:15:09,272
Breaking up is always ugly and nasty.

1099
01:15:11,230 --> 01:15:12,855
The opposite of love is hate.

1100
01:15:14,105 --> 01:15:18,522
But Susan and the likes of
you won't understand this,

1101
01:15:18,605 --> 01:15:19,980
because you have never been in love.

1102
01:15:20,063 --> 01:15:20,897
Right?

1103
01:15:25,813 --> 01:15:26,730
You're done?

1104
01:15:27,147 --> 01:15:28,063
I'm full.

1105
01:15:29,397 --> 01:15:30,355
That's right.

1106
01:15:30,772 --> 01:15:32,688
Keep up that attitude.

1107
01:15:33,396 --> 01:15:34,271
Let me finish it.

1108
01:16:17,979 --> 01:16:18,895
Johnston?

1109
01:16:20,062 --> 01:16:21,395
Are you sure I have to get a tattoo?

1110
01:16:21,895 --> 01:16:24,979
Does it have to be "Forever Valentino"?

1111
01:16:25,312 --> 01:16:29,104
The statement said the missing girl
had such a tattoo.

1112
01:16:29,354 --> 01:16:32,937
It's awful. I don't know any Valentino.

1113
01:16:33,020 --> 01:16:34,937
And I don't love Valentino.

1114
01:16:35,270 --> 01:16:37,145
Even the tattooist reminded me
to think twice.

1115
01:16:37,228 --> 01:16:38,562
I'll be stuck with it

1116
01:16:38,812 --> 01:16:39,853
Then forget it.

1117
01:16:40,603 --> 01:16:41,645
We'll stop investigating.

1118
01:17:07,103 --> 01:17:08,061
Vinci Lai.

1119
01:17:09,311 --> 01:17:11,269
<i>Where did you go after you got the tattoo?</i>

1120
01:17:17,852 --> 01:17:20,144
May Wong, where did you go?

1121
01:17:43,644 --> 01:17:46,060
Kay Yeung, where did you go?

1122
01:17:49,852 --> 01:17:52,685
Karen Man, where did you go?

1123
01:17:58,310 --> 01:18:01,310
And Sylvia Choi, where were you?

1124
01:18:06,185 --> 01:18:07,101
Where

1125
01:18:11,268 --> 01:18:12,226
did you all go?

1126
01:19:41,933 --> 01:19:45,891
The murderer is a cab driver

1127
01:19:52,016 --> 01:19:52,891
Where are you going?

1128
01:19:52,974 --> 01:19:53,891
I'll find the taxi driver.

1129
01:19:55,932 --> 01:19:57,724
I'll find the taxi driver.

1130
01:19:57,807 --> 01:19:59,391
How will you do that?

1131
01:20:00,224 --> 01:20:02,349
Tell me the date when they went missing.

1132
01:20:05,890 --> 01:20:09,682
Hannah Leung went missing
on February 1995.

1133
01:20:09,807 --> 01:20:10,932
Speak clearly.

1134
01:20:12,849 --> 01:20:13,890
For the past few days.

1135
01:20:14,432 --> 01:20:18,432
I was dumped by you for ten times.
I'm heartbroken.

1136
01:20:18,598 --> 01:20:19,765
But I'm trying my best.

1137
01:20:20,557 --> 01:20:25,598
Hannah Leung, February 7, 1995.

1138
01:20:27,557 --> 01:20:30,848
<i>May Wong, October 11, 1996.</i>

1139
01:20:31,640 --> 01:20:35,473
<i>Karen Man, May 22, 1997.</i>

1140
01:20:36,556 --> 01:20:40,181
<i>Lilian Lee, December 28, 1998.</i>

1141
01:20:40,931 --> 01:20:44,515
<i>Haley Cheung, September 9, 1999.</i>

1142
01:20:45,181 --> 01:20:48,723
<i>Fanny Chan, February 14, 2002.</i>

1143
01:20:49,348 --> 01:20:52,931
<i>Kay Yeung, March 19, 2003.</i>

1144
01:20:53,514 --> 01:20:56,889
<i>Hilda Ko, August 25, 2004.</i>

1145
01:20:57,806 --> 01:21:01,139
<i>Vinci Lai, November 30, 2005.</i>

1146
01:21:02,222 --> 01:21:04,889
<i>Sylvia Choi, January 12, 2006.</i>

1147
01:21:05,389 --> 01:21:09,306
And Minnie, June 20, 1997.

1148
01:21:17,180 --> 01:21:19,222
The murderer didn't commit
any crime in 2000 and 2001.

1149
01:21:20,555 --> 01:21:23,430
And no more such cases after 2006.

1150
01:21:24,805 --> 01:21:26,097
What happened to the murderer?

1151
01:21:27,639 --> 01:21:31,222
Did I have enough money for the taxi?

1152
01:21:31,305 --> 01:21:34,180
You're heartbroken.
It didn't come across your mind.

1153
01:21:34,513 --> 01:21:36,763
Why was I heartbroken?

1154
01:21:37,388 --> 01:21:40,805
These other girls broke up
with their boyfriends.

1155
01:21:40,888 --> 01:21:42,430
I'm unlike them.

1156
01:21:43,138 --> 01:21:44,596
You're close friends.

1157
01:21:44,721 --> 01:21:46,846
You're heartbroken
because she avoided you.

1158
01:21:46,971 --> 01:21:49,388
You waited for her
until midnight and took a taxi.

1159
01:21:55,388 --> 01:21:57,388
You must have fallen for her secretly.

1160
01:21:57,513 --> 01:21:58,471
You're a lesbian.

1161
01:21:58,596 --> 01:22:00,929
Not uncommon
for an adolescent girl like you.

1162
01:22:02,388 --> 01:22:03,388
You must be.

1163
01:22:05,096 --> 01:22:06,763
Hello, Szeto Fatbo.

1164
01:22:07,096 --> 01:22:09,054
Hey, this is not a truce.

1165
01:22:09,429 --> 01:22:11,221
Listen, find taxi drivers

1166
01:22:11,304 --> 01:22:14,429
who quit driving between 2000 and 2001.

1167
01:22:30,887 --> 01:22:34,095
Bastard! He didn't come himself.

1168
01:22:35,054 --> 01:22:38,387
I volunteered to come. May I sit down?

1169
01:22:48,553 --> 01:22:49,720
Szeto is very unhappy.

1170
01:22:50,428 --> 01:22:51,762
I don't want him to stay like that.

1171
01:22:53,262 --> 01:22:54,887
It was not quite like you thought.

1172
01:22:56,262 --> 01:22:59,053
There were things even Szeto didn't know.

1173
01:23:08,970 --> 01:23:10,511
<i>The truth is,
when I first saw both of you,</i>

1174
01:23:11,303 --> 01:23:15,303
<i>Szeto was the one I was attracted to.</i>

1175
01:23:16,761 --> 01:23:17,719
I fell for him immediately.

1176
01:23:25,844 --> 01:23:28,636
<i>I planned to go after him
after the dance contest.</i>

1177
01:23:29,219 --> 01:23:30,844
<i>But I haven't seen the two of you again</i>

1178
01:23:31,802 --> 01:23:33,177
<i>until that day.</i>

1179
01:23:33,802 --> 01:23:38,094
Sir, who are you looking for?

1180
01:23:41,886 --> 01:23:43,760
You're not allowed into
the ladies' changing room.

1181
01:23:50,677 --> 01:23:52,135
The man is quite well-built,

1182
01:23:52,219 --> 01:23:53,594
wears a leather jacket, smokes a cigar

1183
01:23:53,677 --> 01:23:55,510
and acts arrogantly.
Do you know what he wants?

1184
01:23:56,594 --> 01:23:57,593
KEE KEI

1185
01:24:22,551 --> 01:24:24,468
Hey, are you all right?

1186
01:24:25,676 --> 01:24:27,551
It's not my fault.
She suddenly dashed out.

1187
01:24:27,634 --> 01:24:28,759
Call the ambulance.

1188
01:24:30,218 --> 01:24:31,051
Don't be afraid.

1189
01:24:31,509 --> 01:24:32,551
I'm Senior Inspector,

1190
01:24:32,926 --> 01:24:34,093
Szeto Fatbo.

1191
01:24:37,759 --> 01:24:38,593
Don't be afraid.

1192
01:24:38,843 --> 01:24:41,384
<i>It turned out the man I admired was</i>

1193
01:24:42,176 --> 01:24:43,759
<i>a Dirty Harry type of cop.</i>

1194
01:24:44,551 --> 01:24:45,759
At that moment,

1195
01:24:48,051 --> 01:24:51,509
I decided to be with that man

1196
01:24:52,342 --> 01:24:54,134
for the rest of my life.

1197
01:24:55,342 --> 01:24:57,259
He's my one life, one love.

1198
01:24:57,342 --> 01:24:58,300
That's enough.

1199
01:24:58,925 --> 01:24:59,967
I get the picture.

1200
01:25:03,884 --> 01:25:05,134
But may I ask one question,

1201
01:25:07,550 --> 01:25:10,759
you said when you saw us,

1202
01:25:11,342 --> 01:25:12,758
the one you got attracted to was him.

1203
01:25:13,550 --> 01:25:14,717
Why?

1204
01:25:15,967 --> 01:25:16,925
He's cool.

1205
01:25:20,300 --> 01:25:22,383
Tell me, who's more good-looking?

1206
01:25:22,467 --> 01:25:24,383
She must be blind.

1207
01:25:25,175 --> 01:25:27,758
She told you she's infatuated with Szeto.

1208
01:25:28,133 --> 01:25:30,341
It's you who thought otherwise.

1209
01:25:30,675 --> 01:25:32,341
It was just your wishful thinking.

1210
01:25:41,216 --> 01:25:42,174
Stand still.

1211
01:25:44,383 --> 01:25:45,383
Eye on the window.

1212
01:25:49,591 --> 01:25:51,591
Imagine yourself as Minnie.

1213
01:25:57,382 --> 01:25:58,382
Slit your wrist.

1214
01:26:02,841 --> 01:26:04,007
It's a real knife.

1215
01:26:04,424 --> 01:26:06,174
You've got nothing to lose
with looks like Susan.

1216
01:26:06,382 --> 01:26:07,549
There will be scars.

1217
01:26:07,632 --> 01:26:10,591
Scars are bad for pretty girls, not Susan.

1218
01:26:10,674 --> 01:26:12,007
Okay!

1219
01:26:29,465 --> 01:26:30,340
How was that?

1220
01:26:32,132 --> 01:26:33,173
How did that feel?

1221
01:26:33,673 --> 01:26:35,548
I overreacted, I must say.

1222
01:26:36,132 --> 01:26:38,465
I do feel sad, but not heartbroken enough.

1223
01:26:38,548 --> 01:26:39,757
It felt a bit forced.

1224
01:26:42,590 --> 01:26:43,465
Got it.

1225
01:26:45,590 --> 01:26:46,548
Once more.

1226
01:26:50,048 --> 01:26:51,131
Just imagine.

1227
01:26:52,840 --> 01:26:54,631
Minnie took after her grandma

1228
01:26:55,465 --> 01:26:57,423
who has completely lost in love, okay?

1229
01:27:00,631 --> 01:27:02,881
You're Minnie. At school...

1230
01:27:02,964 --> 01:27:04,673
you had no friends, but it's all right

1231
01:27:05,798 --> 01:27:07,673
because you only cared for one boy.

1232
01:27:08,798 --> 01:27:11,922
You secretly loved him.
You really liked him.

1233
01:27:13,047 --> 01:27:15,297
Finally, you two started a relationship.

1234
01:27:15,922 --> 01:27:17,339
You guys were happily dating each other.

1235
01:27:18,422 --> 01:27:19,881
But soon, he grew tired of you.

1236
01:27:20,922 --> 01:27:22,589
He decided to break up with you.

1237
01:27:23,839 --> 01:27:24,881
He dumped you,

1238
01:27:25,922 --> 01:27:26,964
you were deeply hurt.

1239
01:27:28,047 --> 01:27:33,005
It hurt so much,
you started to mutilate yourself.

1240
01:27:49,505 --> 01:27:50,713
Enough.

1241
01:27:50,797 --> 01:27:53,172
Stop, Ho!

1242
01:27:53,255 --> 01:27:56,546
Stop!

1243
01:28:03,338 --> 01:28:04,671
Minnie wasn't waiting for you.

1244
01:28:06,213 --> 01:28:08,421
Was someone living upstairs?

1245
01:28:08,505 --> 01:28:11,213
- It's been vacated for a long time.
- I mean, when Minnie used to come here!

1246
01:28:11,463 --> 01:28:12,588
Yes.

1247
01:28:14,254 --> 01:28:16,171
Was it a boy in the same age as Minnie?

1248
01:28:18,213 --> 01:28:19,129
Yes.

1249
01:28:19,588 --> 01:28:21,421
Did he study in the same school?
Was he good-looking?

1250
01:28:22,504 --> 01:28:23,379
Yes!

1251
01:28:24,129 --> 01:28:25,129
<i>Where is he?</i>

1252
01:28:41,170 --> 01:28:43,170
Grilled Jumbo Prawn. Please enjoy.

1253
01:28:43,837 --> 01:28:44,712
Thank you.

1254
01:28:45,795 --> 01:28:46,754
This way.

1255
01:28:48,504 --> 01:28:49,837
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

1256
01:28:51,420 --> 01:28:52,420
Do you want a drink?

1257
01:28:52,795 --> 01:28:54,503
- Iced sake, please.
- Sure.

1258
01:28:54,670 --> 01:28:55,628
Thank you.

1259
01:29:03,587 --> 01:29:05,170
Did you live in Hong Kong?

1260
01:29:05,587 --> 01:29:06,878
Durham Street in Kowloon Tong?

1261
01:29:07,837 --> 01:29:08,753
Yes.

1262
01:29:10,670 --> 01:29:12,545
Are you Joe?

1263
01:29:14,086 --> 01:29:15,045
You are...

1264
01:29:15,211 --> 01:29:18,378
- Ho, I lived downstairs.
- Please enjoy, sir.

1265
01:29:18,711 --> 01:29:19,836
Darkie?

1266
01:29:21,461 --> 01:29:23,253
You looked completely different.

1267
01:29:23,378 --> 01:29:24,961
You have fairer skin now.

1268
01:29:25,128 --> 01:29:26,544
Almost unrecognizable.

1269
01:29:26,628 --> 01:29:27,836
What are you up to?

1270
01:29:27,919 --> 01:29:28,919
You're still picking fights?

1271
01:29:29,378 --> 01:29:30,753
No, I tripped.

1272
01:29:30,836 --> 01:29:33,961
Are you still going after cats
with air guns?

1273
01:29:34,294 --> 01:29:36,336
Of course not. That is kid's stuff.

1274
01:29:36,753 --> 01:29:38,086
Please pick your choice.

1275
01:29:40,211 --> 01:29:41,961
The Beef Set, please.

1276
01:29:42,169 --> 01:29:43,294
Thank you.

1277
01:29:44,252 --> 01:29:45,961
Didn't you emigrate to Brazil?

1278
01:29:47,919 --> 01:29:48,961
In 1997?

1279
01:29:49,127 --> 01:29:50,211
I returned three years ago

1280
01:29:50,711 --> 01:29:52,336
and started this restaurant with a friend.

1281
01:29:52,586 --> 01:29:54,210
- Okay.
- Zhuhai is a good place for business.

1282
01:29:56,877 --> 01:29:58,252
Hey, around the time you left,

1283
01:29:58,669 --> 01:29:59,710
Minnie also disappeared.

1284
01:30:00,127 --> 01:30:01,169
Did you know Minnie?

1285
01:30:01,460 --> 01:30:02,419
Minnie Lee?

1286
01:30:07,419 --> 01:30:10,418
She studied in our school.
She was in the same class as you.

1287
01:30:13,252 --> 01:30:15,877
I can't recall anything.
I probably didn't know her.

1288
01:30:16,752 --> 01:30:17,668
Not at all?

1289
01:30:18,085 --> 01:30:19,585
She used to hang out at my place.

1290
01:30:21,293 --> 01:30:23,960
No, it doesn't ring a bell.

1291
01:30:26,126 --> 01:30:28,168
Fried rice, sir. Please enjoy.

1292
01:30:40,459 --> 01:30:43,459
Excuse me, one more Grilled Jumbo Prawn.

1293
01:30:43,543 --> 01:30:44,459
Of course.

1294
01:30:56,126 --> 01:30:58,001
Johnston, do you want to eat again?

1295
01:31:00,501 --> 01:31:01,751
Joe knew Minnie.

1296
01:31:02,792 --> 01:31:04,876
How did you know?

1297
01:31:05,667 --> 01:31:07,625
He was making the fried rice
when you mentioned Minnie.

1298
01:31:07,959 --> 01:31:09,209
I had a taste. It was too salty.

1299
01:31:09,625 --> 01:31:10,875
So I ordered two more dishes.

1300
01:31:14,292 --> 01:31:16,500
Grilled Jumbo Prawn. Please enjoy.

1301
01:31:17,667 --> 01:31:18,834
<i>The prawn was too dry.</i>

1302
01:31:19,417 --> 01:31:21,292
Scallop, please.

1303
01:31:21,375 --> 01:31:22,375
Coming right up.

1304
01:31:24,875 --> 01:31:26,500
<i>The scallop finally tasted right,</i>

1305
01:31:27,208 --> 01:31:30,125
which means he got distracted
at the mention of Minnie's name.

1306
01:31:30,958 --> 01:31:32,125
I smell something fishy.

1307
01:31:32,708 --> 01:31:35,083
You think I was just enjoying the food?

1308
01:31:35,833 --> 01:31:37,291
What should we do? Should we follow her?

1309
01:31:37,416 --> 01:31:38,291
Keep an eye on him.

1310
01:31:42,208 --> 01:31:44,250
He's coming out, holding a rat cage.

1311
01:31:46,708 --> 01:31:48,333
He's drowning it.

1312
01:31:54,499 --> 01:31:55,708
He's the one who killed Minnie.

1313
01:31:56,749 --> 01:31:59,374
He dismembered her
and threw the body into a trash bin.

1314
01:32:06,374 --> 01:32:08,707
We've been sitting here for hours
reading magazines.

1315
01:32:08,791 --> 01:32:09,874
Who is he waiting for?

1316
01:32:10,374 --> 01:32:14,041
He's not waiting for someone to come.
He's waiting for someone to leave.

1317
01:32:15,582 --> 01:32:16,582
He's also watching somebody.

1318
01:32:25,874 --> 01:32:27,832
Joe's partner is coming down
from the opposite building.

1319
01:32:42,707 --> 01:32:43,748
He settled the bill.

1320
01:32:44,082 --> 01:32:45,248
Let's do that too.

1321
01:32:45,332 --> 01:32:46,248
Bill, please.

1322
01:32:46,957 --> 01:32:48,873
- Bill, please.
- Right away.

1323
01:32:49,040 --> 01:32:51,290
Hurry, give me the bill.

1324
01:32:51,623 --> 01:32:52,915
Excuse me, please wait for a moment.

1325
01:33:03,040 --> 01:33:05,456
Joe went to his partner's building.
What now?

1326
01:33:07,248 --> 01:33:08,623
Let's go and see.

1327
01:33:08,873 --> 01:33:09,748
What about the bill?

1328
01:33:09,831 --> 01:33:11,206
Leave the money on the table.

1329
01:33:22,914 --> 01:33:25,039
He's after the manager of the restaurant.

1330
01:33:25,331 --> 01:33:26,747
Wow, they're making out!

1331
01:33:37,914 --> 01:33:39,455
- What do you like to drink?
- Dragon Well tea.

1332
01:33:39,539 --> 01:33:40,372
Sure.

1333
01:33:44,164 --> 01:33:45,372
He's fucking your wife.

1334
01:33:45,580 --> 01:33:46,539
Come back quickly.

1335
01:33:48,247 --> 01:33:49,622
Is that the girl who wanted the bill?

1336
01:33:49,914 --> 01:33:51,288
Yes, she's pregnant.

1337
01:33:53,247 --> 01:33:54,705
Is Joe's partner coming back?

1338
01:33:59,830 --> 01:34:00,747
He's running back.

1339
01:34:00,997 --> 01:34:02,580
The pregnant woman is Joe's wife.

1340
01:34:21,579 --> 01:34:23,996
Stupid! He's hiding in the balcony.

1341
01:34:32,704 --> 01:34:34,538
Stop fighting.

1342
01:34:41,329 --> 01:34:42,704
The pregnant woman ran outside.

1343
01:34:44,662 --> 01:34:48,704
Stop fighting. Come down.

1344
01:35:03,412 --> 01:35:04,787
Joe has fallen down too.

1345
01:35:14,828 --> 01:35:16,870
Darling!

1346
01:35:17,703 --> 01:35:20,245
My dear, are you all right?

1347
01:35:22,578 --> 01:35:23,661
I got scared.

1348
01:35:24,661 --> 01:35:27,120
I'm fine.

1349
01:35:31,078 --> 01:35:32,495
The pregnant woman has gone crazy.

1350
01:35:33,453 --> 01:35:34,994
